The paper discusses a system for version control and provenance management for data science, which involves collecting and analyzing data from various sources. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to data management, such as cs.DB (Databases), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of a query language, which could also place it in sub-categories related to programming languages and compilers, such as cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
